							<span>23 believers already joined</span>
						</div>
					</div>

					<!-- The Problem Section -->
					<div class="problem-section">
						<h2 class="section-title">The Silent Crisis of Open Source</h2>
						<div class="story-card">
							<p class="story-text">
								<strong>Remember Log4j?</strong> The critical vulnerability that brought down half the internet?
								That library had <span class="highlight">ONE unpaid maintainer</span> working nights and weekends.
							</p>
							<p class="story-text">
								<strong>Remember Heartbleed?</strong> The OpenSSL bug that exposed millions of passwords?
								Maintained by <span class="highlight">TWO volunteers</span> in their spare time.
							</p>
							<p class="story-text">
								Right now, the packages your company depends on are maintained by exhausted developers
								choosing between fixing your bugs and feeding their families.
							</p>
						</div>
					</div>

					<!-- Mission Statement -->
					<div class="mission-statement">
						<h2 class="mission-title">Here's How We Fix This Forever</h2>
						<div class="mission-grid">
							<div class="mission-item pulse">
								<div class="mission-icon">‚ö°</div>
								<div class="mission-number">30 sec</div>
								<p>From bug report to funded fix. One click, AI estimates cost, payment flows instantly.</p>
							</div>
							<div class="mission-item pulse" style="animation-delay: 0.2s">
								<div class="mission-icon">üåç</div>
								<div class="mission-number">$0</div>
								<p>Tax paperwork for developers. Stripe handles everything. Work from anywhere, get paid everywhere.</p>
							</div>
							<div class="mission-item pulse" style="animation-delay: 0.4s">
								<div class="mission-icon">üí∞</div>
								<div class="mission-number">95%</div>
								<p>Goes to developers. Only 5% platform fee - less than any freelance platform.</p>
							</div>
						</div>
						<p class="mission-text">
							<strong>This isn't charity.</strong> It's fixing a broken economic model. 
							Companies spend <span class="highlight">$500B/year</span> on software that depends on unpaid volunteers.
							PRiority creates the missing market mechanism - turning gratitude into groceries, 
							appreciation into apartment rent, and GitHub stars into actual sustainability.
						</p>
					</div>
					
					<!-- Social Proof Section -->
